<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - 12/06/1994 and After - REMOVE AND INSTALL - LOW AND
        HIGH PRESSURE CUT-OFF SWITCH
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>LOW AND HIGH PRESSURE CUT-OFF SWITCH</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove Low Pressure Cut-Off Switch</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch is off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove lower right instrument panel cover, heater-A/C assembly cover and drain tray.
                    Refer to REMOVE AND INSTALL,
                    <hotlnk document="s16016_HL1601607.xml" xrefid="hl1601607">LOWER RIGHT INSTRUMENT PANEL, HEATER-A/C
                        ASSEMBLY COVER AND DRAIN TRAY
                    </hotlnk>
                    . This will expose the low pressure switch.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connector from the switch (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601626">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601626" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601626" filename="../figg16/G1601626.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="352px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 26. Disconnect Electrical Connector From Switch</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The low pressure cut-off switch can be removed without discharging the refrigerant from
                    the system (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601627">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601627" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601627" filename="../figg16/G1601627.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 27. Remove Low Pressure Cut-Off Switch</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>High Pressure Cut-Off Switch</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The high pressure cut-off switch is located on the expansion valve on the engine side of
                    the dash panel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601628">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601628" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601628" filename="../figg16/G1601628.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 28. High Pressure Cut-Off Switch</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connector from the switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">The high pressure cut-off switch can be removed (threaded out) of the expansion valve
                    without discharging the refrigerant from the system.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install Low Pressure Cut-Off Switch</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring, and lubricate the O-ring and switch threads with
                    <emph type="bold">MINERAL-BASED</emph>
                    refrigerant oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the low pressure cut-off switch in the threaded opening in the evaporator low
                    pressure tube. Tighten to 7 to 15 ft-lbs. (9.5 to 20 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the electrical connector to the switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install lower right instrument panel cover, heater-A/C assembly cover and drain tray.
                    Refer to REMOVE AND INSTALL,
                    <hotlnk document="s16016_HL1601607.xml" xrefid="hl1601607">LOWER RIGHT INSTRUMENT PANEL, HEATER-A/C
                        ASSEMBLY COVER AND DRAIN TRAY</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>High Pressure Cut-Off Switch</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new O-ring, and lubricate the O-ring and switch threads with
                    <emph type="bold">MINERAL-BASED</emph>
                    refrigerant oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the high pressure cut-off switch into the threaded opening in the end of the
                    expansion valve. Tighten to 7 to 15 ft-lbs. (9.5 to 20 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the electrical connector to the switch.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
